---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import CommandTable from '../components/CommandTable.astro';
import WorkflowDiagram from '../components/WorkflowDiagram.astro';
import { Code } from 'astro:components';

const frontmatterFields = [
  { command: 'to', description: 'Recipient address(es). Required. Comma-separated for multiple.' },
  { command: 'cc', description: 'Carbon copy address(es). Optional.' },
  { command: 'bcc', description: 'Blind carbon copy address(es). Optional.' },
  { command: 'subject', description: 'Email subject line. Required.' },
  { command: 'status', description: 'Workflow state: draft, approved, sent, inbox, or archived. Required.' },
  { command: 'from', description: 'Sender address. Optional -- overrides default_from from config.' },
  { command: 'reply_to', description: 'Reply-to address. Optional.' },
  { command: 'attachments', description: 'List of absolute file paths to attach. Optional.' },
];

const basicDraft = `---
to: recipient@example.com
cc: optional@example.com
bcc: hidden@example.com
subject: "Your subject line"
status: draft
from: alternate@example.com
reply_to: reply@example.com
attachments:
  - /path/to/file.pdf
---

Email body in **Markdown** format.`;

const replyExample = `---
to: original-sender@example.com
subject: "Re: Original subject"
status: draft
in_reply_to: "<message-id@example.com>"
references: "<message-id@example.com>"
---

Your reply goes here.

{{SIGNATURE}}

> On 2026-01-15, sender wrote:
>
> Original message text quoted here.`;

const forwardExample = `---
to: ""
subject: "Fwd: Original subject"
status: draft
attachments:
  - /path/to/original-attachment.pdf
---

Your note to the recipient.

{{SIGNATURE}}

---------- Forwarded message ----------
From: Original Sender <sender@example.com>
Date: 2026-01-15
Subject: Original subject
To: you@example.com

Original message body here.`;

const signatureExample = `<div style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">
<p style="margin: 0;">
<b>Your Name</b><br>
Title | Organization<br>
your.name@example.com
</p>
</div>`;

const attachmentStructure = `inbox/2024-01-01-1200_sender_subject.md
inbox/2024-01-01-1200_sender_subject.html
inbox/2024-01-01-1200_sender_subject_attachments/
  document.pdf
  image.png`;

const attachmentFrontmatter = `---
from: sender@example.com
subject: "Document delivery"
status: inbox
has_attachments: true
attachments:
  - "document.pdf"
  - "image.png"
---`;

const sentExample = `---
to: recipient@example.com
subject: "Project update"
status: sent
sent_at: "2026-04-22T10:30:00Z"
sent_via: "mailypoppins 0.6.0"
message_id: "<unique-id@example.com>"
---

Email body here.`;
---

<Layout title="Draft Format -- mailypoppins" description="Markdown email drafts with YAML frontmatter -- fields, status workflow, attachments, and signatures.">
  <Nav />
  <main id="main-content" class="content page">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Draft Format</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Markdown email drafts with YAML frontmatter.</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2 id="basic-format">Basic Format</h2>
      <p>
        Email drafts are plain Markdown files with YAML frontmatter. The frontmatter holds
        metadata (recipients, subject, status), and the body below the second <code>---</code>
        is the email content written in Markdown, which gets converted to HTML when sent.
      </p>
      <Code code={basicDraft} lang="markdown" theme="catppuccin-mocha" />
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="frontmatter-fields">Frontmatter Fields</h2>
      <CommandTable commands={frontmatterFields} />
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="status-workflow">Status Workflow</h2>
      <p>
        Emails follow a strict workflow. Only approved emails can be sent -- the <code>send</code>
        command rejects drafts that have not been approved first. Inbox emails follow a separate
        path from inbox to archived.
      </p>
      <WorkflowDiagram />
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="after-sending">After Sending</h2>
      <p>
        When an email is sent, the file is updated in-place. The <code>status</code> changes
        to <code>sent</code>, and three fields are added: <code>sent_at</code> (ISO 8601 timestamp),
        <code>sent_via</code> (tool version), and <code>message_id</code> (the RFC 822 Message-ID,
        used for sync deduplication). If a sent directory is configured, the file is moved there.
      </p>
      <Code code={sentExample} lang="markdown" theme="catppuccin-mocha" />
      <p>
        The raw RFC 822 message is also appended to the server-side Sent folder
        via IMAP APPEND with the <code>\Seen</code> flag. This is best-effort -- a failed
        APPEND is logged but does not fail the send.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="reply-drafts">Reply Drafts</h2>
      <p>
        Reply drafts are created with <code>mp reply</code> (or <code>r</code>/<code>R</code>
        in the TUI). They include <code>in_reply_to</code> and <code>references</code>
        headers for proper threading, and a <code>{"{{SIGNATURE}}"}</code> placeholder between the reply
        area and the quoted original message.
      </p>
      <p>
        When sent, the placeholder is replaced with the configured signature HTML.
        If the placeholder is removed, the signature falls back to being appended at the end.
      </p>
      <Code code={replyExample} lang="markdown" theme="catppuccin-mocha" />
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="forward-drafts">Forward Drafts</h2>
      <p>
        Forward drafts are created with <code>mp forward</code> (or <code>w</code> in the TUI).
        The <code>to:</code> field is left empty for you to fill in. The subject gets a
        "Fwd:" prefix, and any attachments from the original email are listed in the
        <code>attachments:</code> array with their absolute file paths.
      </p>
      <Code code={forwardExample} lang="markdown" theme="catppuccin-mocha" />
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="signatures">Signatures</h2>
      <p>
        Signatures are HTML snippet files referenced in <code>config.toml</code> under
        the <code>[signatures]</code> section. A default signature name is set with
        <code>signatures.default</code>, and each named entry has a <code>path</code>
        to the HTML file (supports <code>~</code> expansion).
      </p>
      <p>
        For regular drafts, the signature is appended after the email body.
        For reply and forward drafts, the <code>{"{{SIGNATURE}}"}</code> placeholder controls
        placement -- the signature appears between your message and the quoted/forwarded content.
      </p>
      <Code code={signatureExample} lang="html" theme="catppuccin-mocha" />
      <p>
        Use <code>-s &lt;name&gt;</code> to select a specific signature, or
        <code>--no-signature</code> to skip it entirely.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="attachments">Attachments</h2>
      <p>
        Incoming attachments are saved next to the <code>.md</code> file in a
        <code>_attachments/</code> subdirectory. The frontmatter records filenames only (not paths),
        and a <code>has_attachments</code> flag is set to <code>true</code>.
      </p>
      <Code code={attachmentStructure} lang="text" theme="catppuccin-mocha" />
      <Code code={attachmentFrontmatter} lang="yaml" theme="catppuccin-mocha" />
      <p>
        The <code>_attachments/</code> directory is moved or deleted alongside the
        <code>.md</code> and <code>.html</code> companion files during archive, delete, sync
        move, and reconciliation operations. In the TUI, press <code>o</code> to open
        an attachment in the default app, or <code>O</code> to save attachments to a
        chosen directory.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page {
    padding-top: var(--space-16);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-subtext0);
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
</style>
